			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Coal ash, also referred to as coal combustion residuals or CCRs, is produced primarily from the burning of coal in coal-fired power plants. It includes a number of by-products produced from burning coal, such as Fly ash, a very fine, powdery material composed mostly of silica. It is the mineral residue that remains from burning coal. Exposure to coal ash and to the toxic substances it contains may pose a health risk to workers in coal-fired power plants and residents living near coal ash disposal sites.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">煤灰也称为燃煤残渣或 CCR，主要产生于燃煤发电厂的燃煤过程。它包括燃煤产生的许多副产品，例如粉煤灰，一种非常细的粉状物质，主要由二氧化硅组成。它是煤炭燃烧后残留的矿物残渣。接触煤灰及其所含的有毒物质可能会对燃煤发电厂的工人和煤灰处理场附近的居民造成健康风险。</common:generalComment>
